VALUES
(53, 1, 1, 47, 1, 19, 19, 'Paul, and Silvanus, and Timotheus', 'Connection of Paul and Associates', 'Both passages emphasize the involvement of Paul, Silvanus, and Timotheus in preaching to the church. This connection highlights their collective role in spreading the message of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 1, 44, 16, 1, 1, 'Timotheus', 'Connection of Timotheus in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize Timotheus as a key figure. In 2 Thessalonians, he is mentioned alongside Paul and Silvanus, indicating his role in the early church. Acts identifies him as a disciple, highlighting his significance in the ministry.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 1, 52, 1, 1, 10, 'the church of the Thessalonians', 'Connection of Greetings and Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize the greeting to the church of the Thessalonians, highlighting their relationship with God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. Additionally, they express gratitude for the faith and works of the Thessalonians, showcasing a continuity in Paul''s encouragement.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 2, 45, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a common greeting structure used by Paul in his letters.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 2, 46, 1, 3, 3, NULL, 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a common greeting in Pauline letters.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 2, 46, 1, 8, 8, 'Grace unto you, and peace', 'Grace and Blamelessness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of divine support in maintaining a blameless state. The grace mentioned in 2 Thessalonians is foundational for being confirmed blameless in 1 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 61, 3, 18, 18, 'your faith groweth exceedingly', 'Growth in Faith and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth in both passages. 2 Thessalonians emphasizes the growth of faith and charity, while 2 Peter encourages growth in grace and knowledge.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 61, 1, 5, 10, 'the charity of every one of you all toward each other aboundeth', 'Faith and Charity Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of faith and charity among believers. In 2 Thessalonians, the charity of believers abounds, while 2 Peter encourages adding charity to faith, highlighting the importance of these virtues in Christian life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 20, 4, 18, 18, 'faith groweth exceedingly', 'Growth in Faith and Light', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of growth and illumination. In 2 Thessalonians, the faith of the brethren grows exceedingly, while Proverbs describes the path of the just shining more and more, suggesting a parallel in spiritual development.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 23, 40, 29, 31, 'your faith groweth exceedingly', 'Strength and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of strength in the face of challenges. In 2 Thessalonians, the growth of faith leads to an abundance of charity, while Isaiah speaks of renewing strength for those who wait on the Lord.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 50, 1, 9, 9, 'the charity of every one of you', 'Abounding Love and Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love and charity growing among believers. In 2 Thessalonians, the charity of believers is highlighted, while Philippians focuses on love abounding in knowledge and judgment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 52, 4, 1, 1, NULL, 'Faith and Abounding Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of abounding, with 2 Thessalonians highlighting the growth of faith and charity, while 1 Thessalonians encourages believers to abound more in their walk to please God. This connection highlights the importance of increasing spiritual virtues in the Christian life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 3, 52, 4, 9, 10, 'charity of every one of you', 'Connection of Love and Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love among believers. In 2 Thessalonians, the charity of each member abounds, while 1 Thessalonians encourages them to increase their love more and more.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 58, 10, 36, 36, 'patience and faith in all your persecutions', 'Patience in Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of patience during trials. 2 Thessalonians highlights enduring persecutions, while Hebrews stresses the need for patience to receive God''s promise.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 59, 5, 7, 8, 'patience and faith in all your persecutions', 'Patience in Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of patience during trials. 2 Thessalonians highlights enduring persecutions, while James encourages patience as believers await the Lord''s coming.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 58, 12, 1, 3, 'patience and faith in all your persecutions', 'Endurance in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of endurance in the face of trials. 2 Thessalonians highlights patience and faith during persecutions, while Hebrews encourages believers to run with patience the race set before them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 47, 7, 14, 14, 'glory in you in the churches', 'Connection of Boasting and Endurance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of boasting in the faith and endurance of believers. In 2 Thessalonians, the glory in the patience and faith during tribulations is echoed in 2 Corinthians, where boasting about the truth of believers is affirmed.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 52, 2, 14, 14, 'your patience and faith in all your persecutions', 'Suffering and Endurance in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering endured by believers. They highlight the patience and faith of the churches of God in the face of persecution, linking the experiences of the Thessalonians to those of the Judean churches.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 52, 1, 3, 3, 'patience', 'Connection of Patience and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of patience in the face of challenges. 1 Thessalonians highlights ''patience of hope,'' while 2 Thessalonians commends ''patience and faith'' during persecutions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 4, 45, 5, 3, 5, 'tribulations that ye endure', 'Connection of Patience and Tribulation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorying in tribulations and the resulting patience. They highlight how enduring tribulations leads to growth in faith and hope.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 50, 1, 28, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Suffering and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of suffering as a sign of divine judgment or salvation. They present the experiences of believers in the face of adversaries as tokens of their standing before God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 44, 14, 22, 22, 'worthy of the kingdom of God', 'Suffering and the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of suffering as a pathway to being counted worthy of the kingdom of God. They highlight the idea that tribulation is integral to the Christian experience in relation to God''s judgment.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 42, 20, 35, 35, 'counted worthy of the kingdom of God', 'Worthy of the Kingdom Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''accounted worthy'' in both passages. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being counted worthy of the kingdom of God, while Luke discusses those who are accounted worthy to obtain that world.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 66, 19, 2, 2, 'righteous judgment of God', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the righteousness of God''s judgments. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being counted worthy through suffering, while Revelation declares the truth of God''s judgments against corruption and vengeance for His servants.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 19, 99, 4, 4, 'righteous judgment of God', 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment and righteousness. 2 Thessalonians speaks of God''s righteous judgment, while Psalms highlights the king''s love for judgment and equity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 24, 9, 24, 24, 'righteous judgment of God', 'Righteous Judgment and Understanding God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding God''s judgment and righteousness. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being counted worthy through suffering, while Jeremiah highlights God''s delight in exercising judgment and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 5, 42, 21, 36, 36, 'counted worthy of the kingdom of God', 'Worthy of God''s Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of being counted worthy in both passages. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being counted worthy of the kingdom of God, while Luke emphasizes being accounted worthy to escape future trials.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 38, 2, 8, 8, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice and Protection', 'This connection highlights God''s promise to protect His people and bring justice against their oppressors. Both passages emphasize that those who harm God''s people will face consequences, as seen in the recompense of tribulation and the notion of being the ''apple of his eye.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 51, 3, 25, 25, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the principle of divine justice, where wrongdoing is met with recompense. 2 Thessalonians highlights God''s righteous recompense for those who trouble others, while Colossians states that wrongdoers will receive consequences for their actions.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 5, 32, 41, 43, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Vengeance and Justice', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in rendering vengeance against enemies and rewarding those who suffer tribulation. They highlight the theme of divine justice where God avenges His people and punishes their adversaries.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 19, 94, 20, 23, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice Against Iniquity', 'Both passages emphasize God''s righteous response to wrongdoing. 2 Thessalonians speaks of recompensing tribulation, while Psalms declares that the Lord will bring upon them their own iniquity.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 2, 23, 22, 22, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice Against Adversaries', 'This connection highlights God''s promise to act against those who trouble His people. Both passages emphasize God''s role as an adversary to enemies, ensuring justice for the faithful.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 19, 74, 22, 23, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice Against Oppressors', 'This connection highlights God''s response to those who trouble His people. Both passages emphasize God''s righteous action against enemies and the increasing tumult they cause.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 6, 23, 49, 26, 26, 'recompense tribulation to them that trouble you', 'Divine Justice Against Oppressors', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine retribution against those who oppress others. Both passages emphasize God''s righteous response to tribulation and oppression, illustrating that He will bring justice to those who trouble His people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 66, 14, 13, 13, 'rest with us', 'Rest and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of rest for believers. Both passages emphasize the promise of rest in the context of the Lord''s revelation and the assurance of eternal peace for those who die in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 40, 16, 27, 27, 'with his mighty angels', 'Connection of Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord with angels. They highlight the theme of divine revelation and the subsequent rewarding of individuals based on their actions.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 65, 1, 14, 15, NULL, 'Judgment and the Lord''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord to execute judgment. They highlight the role of Jesus and the saints in this event, linking the themes of divine revelation and accountability for ungodly actions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 66, 22, 16, 16, 'when the Lord Jesus shall be revealed', 'Connection of Angelic Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of angels in both passages. In 2 Thessalonians, the Lord Jesus is revealed with ''mighty angels,'' while in Revelation, Jesus sends ''mine angel'' to testify.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 40, 25, 31, 31, 'with his mighty angels', 'Connection of Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the return of Jesus accompanied by angels. They highlight the theme of divine revelation and the establishment of His glory.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 56, 2, 13, 13, 'when the Lord Jesus shall be revealed', 'Connection of Hope and Appearing', 'Both passages emphasize the anticipation of Jesus'' return. 2 Thessalonians speaks of His revelation, while Titus highlights the glorious appearing of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 7, 23, 57, 2, 2, 'rest with us', 'Rest and Peace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rest for the troubled. In 2 Thessalonians, the promise of rest is linked to the revelation of Jesus, while Isaiah speaks of entering into peace and resting in uprightness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 60, 4, 17, 17, 'obey not the gospel', 'Judgment and the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment for those who do not obey the gospel. Both passages emphasize the consequences for those who reject the message of God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 61, 3, 7, 7, 'flaming fire taking vengeance', 'Judgment and Fire Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment through fire. 2 Thessalonians speaks of vengeance in flaming fire, while 2 Peter describes the heavens and earth reserved unto fire for the day of judgment.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 58, 10, 27, 27, 'flaming fire taking vengeance', 'Judgment and Fiery Indignation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment through fire against those who do not know God or obey the gospel. The imagery of ''fiery indignation'' in Hebrews parallels the ''flaming fire'' in 2 Thessalonians, highlighting the seriousness of divine retribution.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 19, 79, 6, 6, 'know not God', 'Divine Wrath on the Unknowing', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine vengeance against those who do not know God. Both passages emphasize the consequences for those who fail to acknowledge or obey the Lord.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 40, 25, 41, 41, 'taking vengeance on them that know not God', 'Connection of Divine Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''everlasting fire'' as a consequence for those who do not obey God. This connection highlights the theme of divine vengeance against those who reject the gospel.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 45, 2, 7, 8, 'obey not the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Judgment and Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of disobedience to God. 2 Thessalonians speaks of vengeance on those who ''know not God,'' while Romans contrasts eternal life for those who obey the truth with wrath for the contentious.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 8, 45, 6, 16, 16, 'obey not the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Obedience and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience and its consequences. Both passages emphasize the importance of whom one obeys, linking disobedience to negative outcomes and obedience to righteousness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 40, 25, 41, 41, 'everlasting destruction', 'Connection of Eternal Punishment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting punishment. 2 Thessalonians speaks of ''everlasting destruction,'' while Matthew refers to ''everlasting fire,'' highlighting a similar theme of eternal consequence for the unrighteous.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 66, 14, 10, 11, 'everlasting destruction from the presence of the Lord', 'Eternal Punishment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of everlasting punishment for the wicked. They describe torment and destruction as consequences of rejecting God, highlighting the severity of divine judgment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 53, 2, 8, 8, 'everlasting destruction from the presence of the Lord', 'Destruction and Revelation of the Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of destruction associated with the Lord''s power. The ''everlasting destruction'' in the first passage connects to the ''destroy'' in the second, highlighting the fate of the wicked at Christ''s coming.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 66, 21, 8, 8, 'everlasting destruction', 'Eternal Punishment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of punishment for the wicked. 2 Thessalonians speaks of ''everlasting destruction,'' while Revelation describes the ''lake which burneth with fire and brimstone.'' This connection highlights the serious consequences for those who reject God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 23, 2, 21, 21, 'the glory of his power', 'Connection of Divine Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the Lord and His glory. They highlight the consequences of divine presence, with 2 Thessalonians speaking of punishment and Isaiah depicting fear in the face of God''s majesty.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 50, 3, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Destruction Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of destruction. 2 Thessalonians speaks of ''everlasting destruction,'' while Philippians refers to ''end is destruction,'' highlighting a thematic link regarding consequences for those who prioritize earthly matters.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 9, 40, 7, 23, 23, 'everlasting destruction', 'Eternal Punishment and Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of being separated from God. 2 Thessalonians speaks of ''everlasting destruction'' while Matthew describes being told to ''depart from me.'' This connection highlights the theme of divine rejection for those who do not know Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 43, 17, 10, 10, 'glorified in his saints', 'Glorification in Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification in relation to believers. Both passages emphasize the glorification of Jesus and the saints, indicating a shared focus on divine admiration and unity among believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 46, 3, 13, 13, 'in that day', 'Connection of Judgment Day Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of ''that day'' when believers'' works will be revealed. 2 Thessalonians speaks of Christ''s glorification in His saints, while 1 Corinthians discusses the testing of each man''s work on that day.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 49, 1, 18, 18, 'glorified in his saints', 'Glory and Inheritance in Saints', 'Both passages emphasize the glory associated with the saints. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being glorified in his saints, while Ephesians refers to the riches of the glory of his inheritance in the saints.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 55, 4, 8, 8, 'in that day', 'Connection of Righteousness and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the reward given at ''that day'' for believers. They highlight the glorification of the Lord and the righteousness bestowed upon those who love His appearing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 23, 49, 3, 3, 'to be glorified', 'Glorification of the Servant', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification in both passages. In 2 Thessalonians, believers are to be glorified in Christ, while Isaiah speaks of God''s glorification in His servant, Israel.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 4, 23, 23, 23, NULL, 'Divine Glory and Protection', 'Both passages emphasize God''s glory and the protection of His people. In 2 Thessalonians, the glorification of saints reflects God''s work among believers, while Numbers highlights God''s safeguarding of Jacob and Israel, showcasing His power. This connection highlights the assurance of divine favor and admiration.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 10, 60, 2, 9, 9, 'glorified in his saints', 'Glorification and Praise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of believers and their role in praising God. 2 Thessalonians speaks of being glorified in saints, while 1 Peter highlights showing forth praises. This connection highlights the transformative impact of faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 50, 2, 13, 13, 'good pleasure of his goodness', 'Connection of God''s Good Pleasure', 'Both passages emphasize God''s role in fulfilling his good pleasure in believers. 2 Thessalonians speaks of God''s goodness and work of faith, while Philippians highlights God working in believers to accomplish his will.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 51, 1, 9, 13, 'count you worthy of this calling', 'Connection of Worthiness and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being counted worthy and the importance of prayer for spiritual growth. They highlight the desire for believers to fulfill God''s calling and to walk in a manner that pleases Him, demonstrating a shared focus on spiritual empowerment and good works.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 52, 1, 3, 3, 'work of faith', 'Connection of Faith and Work', 'Both passages emphasize the ''work of faith'' as a central theme. In 2 Thessalonians, the prayer is for God to fulfill the ''work of faith with power,'' which resonates with the remembrance of the ''work of faith'' in 1 Thessalonians.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 52, 3, 9, 13, 'work of faith with power', 'Connection of Prayer and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and the desire for the growth of faith among believers. 2 Thessalonians 1:11 speaks of fulfilling the work of faith, while 1 Thessalonians 3:10 mentions perfecting what is lacking in faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 53, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Worthy of God''s Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize being counted worthy, linking the believer''s calling and suffering to their worthiness for God''s kingdom. This connection highlights the importance of faith and divine approval in the life of believers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 53, 2, 14, 14, 'worthy of this calling', 'Connection of Calling and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being called by God. The first verse speaks of being counted worthy of a calling, while the second highlights being called to obtain the glory of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 11, 50, 1, 9, 11, 'fulfil all the good pleasure of his goodness', 'Connection of Prayer and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer for spiritual growth and the fulfillment of God''s purposes. They highlight the desire for believers to be filled with goodness and righteousness, aligning with God''s calling.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 53, 1, 10, 10, 'glorified in you', 'Glorification of Jesus in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of Jesus in relation to believers. In 2 Thessalonians 1:10, it speaks of Jesus being glorified in his saints, while 1:12 highlights the glorification of Jesus in believers through grace.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 43, 17, 10, 10, 'glorified in you', 'Glorification of Christ in Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorification in both passages. 2 Thessalonians emphasizes the glorification of Jesus in believers, while John states that Jesus is glorified in them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 60, 4, 14, 14, 'the name of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Glorification in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of Christ and believers. In 2 Thessalonians, the focus is on the glory of Jesus in believers, while 1 Peter highlights the joy and glory that comes from suffering for His name.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 47, 13, 4, 4, 'the name of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Glorification and Power in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the power of God in relation to believers'' lives. 2 Thessalonians speaks of glorification through grace, while 2 Corinthians highlights living by God''s power despite weakness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 46, 1, 4, 4, 'grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the grace of God given through Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the importance of glorifying the Lord and receiving His grace.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Grace and Glorification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, highlighting how his grace leads to glorification and richness in believers. The transformation from poverty to richness in 2 Corinthians reflects the glorification mentioned in 2 Thessalonians.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(53, 1, 12, 50, 2, 9, 11, 'the name of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Glorification of Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the glorification of Jesus Christ. In 2 Thessalonians, it states that the name of Jesus may be glorified in believers, while Philippians declares that God has highly exalted Him, leading to universal acknowledgment of His lordship.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
